4:
Ayyy, Techtus! My man! Congrats on
hitting the top bracket in the ring!
6:
Techie, it's youuu! You're going to be
great at tonight's match, I just know
it!
14: Hey, guys. Did you hear all that?
18:
I've come a long way, huh? Ol'
Techtus is a certified top-ranker
now. A hero of the stadium!
21:
I'm glad you're happy... But is this
really what you want? Are you not
forgetting your old life and old world?
26:
Ah... I'm not forgetting anything... I've
been saving the prize money from
the matches I've been in.
28:
...I've almost got enough money to
restore my body to how it was
before.
33:
Wow, really? So you'll be going back
as soon as you've saved up enough?
38:
...Let's not worry about that right
now! I want to hear what you think
of the CURRENT me!
40:
The new me is almost
unrecognizable compared to the
old me, right? Like I've grown up, or
got more mature, or something—
50:
S-so harsh! Come on, you're my
friend! It couldn't hurt to compliment
me a little more!
54:
Do you have any idea how much
you've been pulling us around lately?
59:
Going out on journeys, forming a
band... You're always having us tag
along.
64:
Okay, sorry, sorry! It was wrong of
me to fish for praise like how I've
been doing!
67:
...I guess my growth won't be
obvious unless I put it on full display!
71:
I hope you've got high hopes for
tonight's matches! I'm going to show
you the incredible limits of a
top-ranker!
75:
Looking forward to it. I've got money
on you, after all.
80: You're placing bets on a friend?!
84:
...Well, anyway! I'll do my best, so I
hope you all have a good time!
88:
And that's it! Our new star Techtus
takes the win! Even among top-rank
opponents, he can't stop winning!
92:
That was close... Looks like I'm really
in the big leagues now. I think my
face got a little singed...
96:
...No, I've gotta look cool! Everyone's
watching me!
104: What the hell are you doing?!
107:
It's not me! My control unit's gone
haywire, and I can't control the
output either! Even these dummy
rounds could be lethal!
117:
Th-this is an emergency! All guests,
please follow staff instructions and—
134:
Everyone! Please stop pushing and
form a line!
151:
A top-ranker like me... I have a
responsibility to uphold!
160:
If I shoot down every projectile,
nobody will get hurt!
163:
Establishing spatial coordinates...
Complete! All targets locked on!
186:
All right, Mr. Top-Ranker. Give the
audience a little flourish or
something.
190: U-uh... Um! Hey! Is everyone okay?!
194:
N-no, not like that! Er, I mean... If
anyone's injured! Please go to the
hospital right away!
198:
No, that was weird! Everyone! Uh,
please... Crap! What do I say?!
204:
Looks like your opponent from
earlier is doing fine. It seems like
only the weapon systems were
damaged.
206:
...Also, your opponent wanted to say
thank you for saving the day.
210:
That's great. You really did a solid
job, huh?
214:
...You're too kind. I really froze up at
the end there... It was super lame.
219:
Come on. That was just you being
you, right?
224:
Huh? What do you mean?
...That's not how everyone sees me,
right?
229:
I like you when you're being yourself.
But, it's pretty funny when you try to
act cool, too.
234:
Th-thank you, I think? I mean, I do
appreciate that!
239:
Techtus. There's a letter for you from
management.
244:
The stadium wants me to pay
damages? Seriously?!
I helped out, didn't I?!
248:
That's Qualia City for you... 
Think you can pay it?
252:
I-if I use the prize money I've saved,
probably...
256:
...Oh, FINE! I'll pay it! I didn't feel like
changing my body back just yet,
anyway!
260:
I'll deal with any regrets later!
Besides, I should be able to get the
money back soon enough as a
top-ranker in the ring!
263:
I'm counting on your support,
everyone! I'll be GENUINELY cool next
time, I promise!
268:
Yeah, yeah. I'll watch with low
expectations.
272:
You asked me earlier how I would
feel if a friend showed up one day
suddenly transformed into an
ultimate weapon.
275:
Well, I'd just ask them "Why'd you do
it?" Now, whether I'd get angry or
laugh at them... I guess it would
depend on what they said next.
278: Is that a good enough answer?
283:
W-wait! What's that supposed to
mean? And why're you answering
that now?!
